In article <CEuBFI.FpB@cix.compulink.co.uk> 
klockstone@cix.compulink.co.uk (Keith Lockstone) writes:
> As an extension to the FAQ, may I suggest that a few conventions 
> are agreed upon and that certain FTP sites maintain a directory 
> of programs that can be used for analysis of crypto products.  

What would you suggest these programs do?  Aside from testing that the
output of a cipher looks like random noise, there is little that can
be done to mechanically analyze a cryptosystem.

> Similarly there would be a need for programs to estimate the 
> strength of block ciphers - starting with a differential 
> cryptanalyser.

A differential cryptanalyzer would have to be rolled anew for each
new algorithm.

